channel.title: AT presents AT's Radio Episode One - Five!
channel.description:
So yeah some of you guys might remember the demos I did a couple of months ago. Well, after self-teaching myself how to mix with Ableton Live (because Audacity really was one hell of a thing to use), I finally finished the first episode!
This one's a "Mixed Mix". Meaning there's more than one genre into it. But later I might make some Lounge Mix or Trance Mix or House Mix, I don't know.
Anyway, here's the download link:
[url='https://download778.mediafire.com/g4gctknplgwg/gng4ytm2mnx/episode1.mp3']https://download778.mediafire.com/g4gctknplgwg/gng4ytm2mnx/episode1.mp3[/url]
Thoughts? Comments? Things I should improve? Should I stop mixing and never think about it again?
Tracklist:
[b]Steve Brian[/b] - [i]La Gomera [Cressidia Remix][/i] [b]U-Tern[/b] - [i]Style, Class, Flair[/i] [b]Deadmau5[/b] -[i] Hi Friend![/i] [b]Tritonal[/b] - [i]Piercing Quiet [Featuring Soto][/i] [b]Signalrunners[/b] - [i]Meet Me in Montauk[/i] [b]Stardust[/b] - [i]Music Sounds Better With You [Bob Sinclar Remix][/i] [b]Djedjotronic[/b] - [i]Gum Attack[/i] [b]Harvard Bass[/b] - [i]Caked[/i] [u]&[/u] [b]Buraka Som Sistema - [i]Kalema[/i][/b] [b]Caspa & Rusko[/b] - [i]Rock Bottom[/i] [b]Orien[/b] - [i]Rainbow Tear Drop[/i] [b]Conquest[/b] - [i]Forvever[/i]

A friend of mine asked me if I could do a mix for a party he had a coule of weeks ago, so I made him one. Many of you will probably dislike the tracks I included, but I think they are as good as anything.
